result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Dylan Lee Walworth in court with attorney Alec Phillip Nocco.  Kristi S. Tlusty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Plea agreement put into the record.  Plea of no contest to count Count` Possession of THC - Case No. 16CM8.  Plea colloquy.  Plea freely, voluntarily and intelligently; factual basis exists.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Court orders court costs; DNA surcharge and sample; 10 days county jail with huber and good time.  Court dismisses and read in remaining counts in 16CM8 and Case No. 16CM9.  Case No. 16TR36 - court enters a deferred agreement - defendant is attending point reduction class.  Case No. 16FO17 - Underage drinking - Defendant enters a plea of guilty; court finds defendant guilty.  Court orders $263.50 forfeiture and 30 day suspension of driver's license - defendant will take underage drinking class in lieu of license suspension.  Court ordered all of Mr. Walworth's obligations are to be added as one payment plan of $100.00 a month beginning May 11, 2016.  - rt
Plea/sentencing hearing on May 9, 2016 at 01:30 pm.
Order for Appearance at Settlement Conference; Report to Court on Results of Settlement Conference.

*Defendant shall not leave the State of Wisconsin without prior notice to and written approval of the Court.  Must report to the Taylor County Sheriff's Office for Booking Procedure.  Defendant shall not possess or consume any controlled substances without a valid prescription.

Defendant Dylan Lee Walworth in court with attorney Alec Phillip Nocco.  Kristi S. Tlusty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Waive reading of complaint, charges and penalties.  Plea of not guilty to all charges.  Court orders $500.00 signature bond; booking; no possession or consumption of controlled substances without a valid prescription.   Pre-trial conference scheduled for March 29, 2016 at 02:15 pm.  - rt
